        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 4:27PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Wilmer, or 12 miles southeast of Lucedale. This
storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wilmer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
